1
00:00:12,262 --> 00:00:15,473
<i>It's been a month since</i>
<i>Min Ho and I officially started dating.</i>

2
00:00:17,475 --> 00:00:19,978
<i>I've always known him</i>
<i>as Min Ho, my friend.</i>

3
00:00:20,061 --> 00:00:22,939
<i>But as Min Ho, my boyfriend?</i>

4
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:26,651
<i>Well, our relationship</i>
<i>just hits different.</i>

5
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:29,654
<i>In the obvious ways.</i>

6
00:00:36,911 --> 00:00:39,164
<i>But in the surprising ways too.</i>

7
00:00:39,247 --> 00:00:42,709
<i>Like, he's a total gentleman. Who knew?</i>

8
00:00:42,792 --> 00:00:46,546
<i>Even though I can get my own </i>banchan,
<i>thank you very much.</i>

9
00:00:46,629 --> 00:00:50,842
<i>But okay, it's sweet that</i>
<i>he pays attention to the little things.</i>

10
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:55,346
<i>I like to think</i>
<i>I'm opening up his world a little too.</i>

11
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:57,140
<i>With my Sunset List, for example,</i>

12
00:00:57,223 --> 00:01:00,060
<i>which he finds</i>
<i>completely embarrassing half the time.</i>

13
00:01:00,143 --> 00:01:04,105
<i>But I'm his girlfriend now, so I get</i>
<i>to make him be embarrassing with me.</i>

14
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:06,024
<i>I think he secretly likes it.</i>

15
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:09,819
<i>We were friends for so long,</i>

16
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:12,614
<i>I thought I knew everything</i>
<i>there is to know about him.</i>

17
00:01:12,697 --> 00:01:15,825
<i>But as it turns out,</i>
<i>we're still getting to know each other.</i>

18
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:19,704
<i>If only a pesky thing called school</i>

19
00:01:19,788 --> 00:01:22,165
<i>would stop getting in the way</i>
<i>of our relationship.</i>

20
00:01:26,669 --> 00:01:30,673
Of course, the hardest class at KISS
is the one I need to graduate.

21
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:33,927
And I get that Jiwon said
no more special cousin favors,

22
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:37,138
but she could at least, like,
pity me for my sucky Korean.

23
00:01:37,222 --> 00:01:39,390
What about me? I'm fluent.

24
00:01:39,891 --> 00:01:42,811
For Monday, read Yi Kwang-su's <i>Mujong,</i>

25
00:01:42,894 --> 00:01:46,314
a ten-page essay
on the Japanese occupation of Korea

26
00:01:46,397 --> 00:01:47,482
for historical context.

27
00:01:49,692 --> 00:01:51,069
Have a good weekend.

28
00:01:55,490 --> 00:02:00,328
Jiwon, I love Korean Lit
as much as the next teen,

29
00:02:00,411 --> 00:02:03,456
but Professor Lee doesn't even assign
this much homework in his class.

30
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:04,666
Oh, I'm aware.

31
00:02:05,166 --> 00:02:07,710
When I showed him my syllabus,
he nearly wept with joy.

32
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:09,254
That's great.

33
00:02:09,337 --> 00:02:14,050
Well, this weekend, Min Ho is shooting
a music video for Eunice's debut single,

34
00:02:14,134 --> 00:02:16,803
and I really want to be there
to support him.

35
00:02:16,886 --> 00:02:21,349
So is there any chance
I could just get a small extension?

36
00:02:21,432 --> 00:02:24,018
No, Kitty. You're already
too focused on your boyfriend

37
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:27,063
and not on what really matters,
this class.

38
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:31,276
<i>I love my cousin, but I am not</i>
<i>a fan of my teacher right now.</i>

39
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:34,696
Hi.

40
00:02:35,238 --> 00:02:38,575
Um, Professor Ahn.
I was just heading to the supply closet.

41
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:42,412
I was wondering if you needed
any Post-it Notes, staples?

42
00:02:42,495 --> 00:02:43,955
I may be new, but I can assure you

43
00:02:44,038 --> 00:02:46,875
that my classroom is well-stocked,
Professor Finnerty.

44
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:52,297
Great. Well, if you did need anything,
my office is just down the, um, hall.

45
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:02,098
<i>How did I not see this sooner?</i>

46
00:03:02,182 --> 00:03:04,809
<i>It's a grumpy sunshine match</i>
<i>made in heaven!</i>

47
00:03:13,776 --> 00:03:18,072
I am telling you,
Alex and my cousin have serious chemistry.

48
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:20,074
- I don't see it.
- Me neither.

49
00:03:20,158 --> 00:03:21,409
What are we talking about?

50
00:03:21,492 --> 00:03:24,120
What a cute couple
Alex and Jiwon are going to make.

51
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:25,955
I shall call them "Jilex."

52
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:27,081
I don't see it.

53
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:30,460
Oh my God, can everyone stop doubting
my matchmaking skills and trust me?

54
00:03:30,543 --> 00:03:33,087
All right, calm down.
Fine, you can do your thing.

55
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:36,341
Besides, we've got a thousand things
to do before Eunice's video shoot.

56
00:03:36,424 --> 00:03:38,927
I can't believe your dad
rented the aquarium for Eunice.

57
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:40,511
Will Baby Moo Moo make a cameo?

58
00:03:40,595 --> 00:03:41,554
Baby who-who?

59
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:44,057
Baby Moo Moo, the newborn manatee,

60
00:03:44,140 --> 00:03:46,935
only the most viral thing
on the planet right now?

61
00:03:47,018 --> 00:03:49,229
Yeah, unfortunately no Baby Moo Moo,

62
00:03:49,312 --> 00:03:51,981
but I did cast Tae-Oh
for Eunice's video shoot.

63
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:54,734
Ew, the handsy limo guy?

64
00:03:54,817 --> 00:03:58,363
I know, he's not exactly my first choice,
but he's Dad's client.

65
00:03:58,446 --> 00:04:01,866
Oh, but guess who's designing
Eunice's costumes?

66
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:05,662
- Yisoo.
- Wow! After my dress fiasco on the yacht?

67
00:04:05,745 --> 00:04:08,873
That's amazing. I didn't think your dad
would get over that, let alone Yisoo.

68
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:10,917
I have no idea what changed her mind,

69
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,211
but Eunice and I are meeting
her new assistant later

70
00:04:13,294 --> 00:04:14,754
to go over costumes.

71
00:04:14,837 --> 00:04:17,882
Well, I have to get going
on my Korean lit homework.

72
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:21,052
But I'd rather spend time with you.

73
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:27,892
- Mm.
- I have to go.

74
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:31,604
Yeah, but what if we squeeze in
a quick Korean lesson?

75
00:04:35,566 --> 00:04:37,318
- Bye.
- Bye.

76
00:04:37,902 --> 00:04:40,363
- Are we that annoying?
- God, I hope not.

77
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:43,783
I was thinking I need a Korean lesson too.

78
00:04:43,866 --> 00:04:45,159
Want me to teach you?

79
00:04:45,243 --> 00:04:46,411
Exactly.

80
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:54,836
It's all about the tongue.

81
00:04:54,919 --> 00:04:55,795
Oh, is it now?

82
00:04:55,878 --> 00:05:02,010
Try to keep the tip of your tongue
lightly pressed behind your front teeth.

83
00:05:05,054 --> 00:05:06,472
What am I even saying anyway?

84
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:09,309
It means, "You are so handsome."

85
00:05:12,103 --> 00:05:15,189
I think I'm going to be…

86
00:05:16,357 --> 00:05:17,483
…sick.

87
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:21,529
- Oh! Is she okay?
- Yeah, she's just stressed.

88
00:05:22,113 --> 00:05:25,491
Honestly, I am as well.
There's a lot riding on her debut.

89
00:05:25,575 --> 00:05:27,535
After all the money
Dad spent on the video,

90
00:05:27,618 --> 00:05:29,579
we really can't afford a flop.

91
00:05:29,662 --> 00:05:31,831
All right, I better go check on her.

92
00:05:33,207 --> 00:05:35,626
By the way, can you keep an eye out
for Yisoo's assistant?

93
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:37,128
She should be here any minute now.

94
00:05:37,211 --> 00:05:40,798
Yeah, and don't be stressed.
You've got this. And I've got you.

95
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:45,970
Okay.

96
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:57,273
<i>Damn. Who is that?</i>

97
00:05:59,025 --> 00:06:00,610
<i>Oh my God, she's coming towards me.</i>

98
00:06:00,693 --> 00:06:01,694
<i>Oh my God, she's here!</i>

99
00:06:01,778 --> 00:06:04,864
Excuse me, by chance
do you know where Min Ho Kang is?

100
00:06:04,947 --> 00:06:06,616
- Oh, um…
- Ah.

101
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:08,242
Sorry, Thought you spoke Korean.

102
00:06:08,326 --> 00:06:10,495
You must be Yisoo's assistant.

103
00:06:10,578 --> 00:06:12,872
- Min Ho's super excited to meet you.
- <i>Noona?</i>

104
00:06:12,955 --> 00:06:15,291
Hey,
you don't come greet your <i>noona?</i>

105
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:22,590
- What are you doing here?
- You know, I just wanted to surprise you.

106
00:06:22,673 --> 00:06:24,050
What a great surprise!

107
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:26,302
You look amazing.
I can't believe you're here!

108
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:30,348
<i>Is it me,</i>
<i>or is Min Ho blushing? Who is this girl?</i>

109
00:06:30,431 --> 00:06:33,643
Uh, my Korean's not perfect,
but I heard you say <i>noona?</i>

110
00:06:33,726 --> 00:06:35,561
Do you already know each other?

111
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:39,982
I'm sorry, Kitty, this is Gigi. She's a

112
00:06:40,942 --> 00:06:42,360
family friend.

113
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:46,823
Wait, so you're working for Yisoo?
I mean, you already had impeccable style.

114
00:06:46,906 --> 00:06:50,118
But this is next level! Does this mean
you're moving back to Seoul?

115
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:52,662
- What happened to FIT?
- Okay, take a breath.

116
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:54,831
That's a cool job
for someone still in college.

117
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:57,083
I took a semester off
after I landed the Yisoo job,

118
00:06:57,166 --> 00:07:00,128
but I had no idea
you were Eunice's manager until--

119
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:04,549
Damn! Did I miss the big reunion?

120
00:07:04,632 --> 00:07:05,466
Mwah.

121
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:09,387
- What's up, Kathy?
- Wait. Is this your doing?

122
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:11,305
Well, when I heard
you were working for Yisoo,

123
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:15,685
I figured you were the perfect person
to get this one back on track.

124
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:18,354
Plus, you two together again? Fire!

125
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:22,024
I can't believe you got Yisoo to give me
and Eunice a second chance.

126
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:24,986
Don't act so surprised.
I'd take a bullet for you.

127
00:07:25,653 --> 00:07:27,947
- Literally.
- <i>Noona… </i>

128
00:07:28,030 --> 00:07:29,073
You're the best.

129
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:31,409
So, I'll see you at the video shoot.

130
00:07:31,492 --> 00:07:32,827
That's the gig.

131
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:36,289
Yisoo fired her part-time third assistant,
so until she hires someone else,

132
00:07:36,372 --> 00:07:37,498
I'm doing both jobs.

133
00:07:37,582 --> 00:07:41,085
That sounds like a huge responsibility
for someone who stole her dad's--

134
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:45,590
I did not steal my dad's Porsche.
<i>We </i>borrowed it.

135
00:07:45,673 --> 00:07:47,008
Yeah, that was a crazy night.

136
00:07:52,722 --> 00:07:54,474
How crazy are we talkin'?

137
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:55,725
Long story.

138
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:58,269
Mm.

139
00:07:59,020 --> 00:08:01,147
So, um, should we go find Eunice?

140
00:08:01,814 --> 00:08:02,857
Bye.

141
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:07,278
Gigi's pretty lush, isn't she?

142
00:08:07,361 --> 00:08:10,323
It'll be great for Min Ho
to have a family friend at the shoot.

143
00:08:10,406 --> 00:08:11,532
The more the merrier.

144
00:08:11,616 --> 00:08:14,577
A family friend?
Is that all you call Gigi?

145
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:16,704
It's just a funny way to put it.

146
00:08:16,787 --> 00:08:18,289
Don't get me wrong, I mean,

147
00:08:18,372 --> 00:08:22,126
Min Ho's family
absolutely adores Gige, but…

148
00:08:22,627 --> 00:08:25,963
You know, his feelings were just
a little bit more intense.

149
00:08:26,047 --> 00:08:29,550
Oh, like, Min Ho used to have
a crush on her or something?

150
00:08:29,634 --> 00:08:31,511
I mean, can you blame him? She's so cool.

151
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:37,350
I mean, hard agree. But just real talk,
she wasn't just a crush.

152
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:40,853
She was Min Ho's first love.

153
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:53,491
Hey. How'd you sleep?

154
00:08:53,574 --> 00:08:56,077
Fine. Did anyone see you sneak out?

155
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:58,621
No, I think the coast was clear.

156
00:08:58,704 --> 00:09:01,332
Oh! I was thinking maybe, if you're free,

157
00:09:01,415 --> 00:09:03,876
would you want to come
to the Zanele Muholi exhibition?

158
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:07,046
Or we could go dancing
at that club in Itaewon.

159
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:11,717
Okay. Okay, let's do culture.

160
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:13,427
- Let's do culture.
- Yeah.

161
00:09:14,512 --> 00:09:16,097
- Okay. I'll see you later.
- Okay, bye.

162
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:30,528
Black sesame latte, right?

163
00:09:31,946 --> 00:09:33,406
I can buy my own coffee.

164
00:09:33,489 --> 00:09:38,744
I'm hoping we can move past
our weirdness for Juliana's sake.

165
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,830
I saw on Instagram you like these,

166
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:43,624
so I figured I'd get you one
as a peace offering.

167
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:45,876
Please take it.

168
00:09:48,212 --> 00:09:50,464
Thanks.

169
00:10:00,391 --> 00:10:02,643
Find anything interesting
on Gigi's socials?

170
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:04,979
Other than photos of her looking chic?

171
00:10:05,062 --> 00:10:09,900
There's one at Nobu with Min Ho's mom,
and one at Coachella with Min Ho's dad.

172
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:12,570
Did I mention that his family loves her?

173
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:16,449
Min Ho is with you now.
Why does any of this matter?

174
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:18,200
I don't know.

175
00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:22,121
Maybe because his dad made it clear
he doesn't think I belong in his world,

176
00:10:22,204 --> 00:10:23,956
and Gigi clearly does.

177
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:26,292
I mean, they both
obviously have all this history,

178
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:30,588
they both speak Korean, and they both look
annoyingly good in jorts. So…

179
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:34,842
- No wonder she was his first love.
- First loves ain't all that.

180
00:10:34,925 --> 00:10:37,762
Really? How long did it take you
to get over Juliana?

181
00:10:37,845 --> 00:10:40,056
I… will let you know.

182
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:41,265
Mm-hmm.

183
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:43,434
Whatever. The only reason
I even brought Gigi up

184
00:10:43,517 --> 00:10:47,229
is because she's looking for someone
to be Yisoo's part-time third assistant.

185
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:48,981
You'd be perfect for the job.

186
00:10:49,065 --> 00:10:52,193
I don't know. I was the one
that put you in that stolen Yisoo dress.

187
00:10:52,276 --> 00:10:55,738
Yes. In hindsight, not your finest moment,
but you had a lot going on that night.

188
00:10:55,821 --> 00:10:58,282
Anyway, you could come with me
to Eunice's video shoot,

189
00:10:58,366 --> 00:11:00,076
help Gigi with the wardrobe stuff.

190
00:11:01,202 --> 00:11:05,122
And assist you in keeping tabs
on Min Ho while Gigi's around?

191
00:11:06,248 --> 00:11:08,626
To be a good assistant,
you gotta learn to multitask.

192
00:11:08,709 --> 00:11:10,920
And to be a good girlfriend,
you gotta chill.

193
00:11:12,546 --> 00:11:15,341
<i>Yuri's right. I'm spiraling for nothing.</i>

194
00:11:15,424 --> 00:11:17,301
<i>Min Ho's always been Team Kitty.</i>

195
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:20,513
<i>And it's about time I show him</i>
<i>I'm Team Min Ho.</i>

196
00:11:32,983 --> 00:11:36,487
- Hey. Uh, Min Ho's just getting ready.
- Ah.

197
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:39,865
I think he's a bit stressed
about the video.

198
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:41,158
Yeah.

199
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:42,868
Oh, and speaking of,

200
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:45,329
I've been thinking about
going to the shoot to support Eunice.

201
00:11:45,413 --> 00:11:46,831
I'm sure she would love that.

202
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,793
- You look amazing.
- Oh.

203
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:52,253
- Hi.
- Hi.

204
00:11:52,336 --> 00:11:53,796
But it's not that kind of date.

205
00:11:53,879 --> 00:11:57,049
Look, I know you're stressed,
so I booked us a spa date.

206
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:59,427
I got your favorite facialist
to do that serumy thing.

207
00:11:59,510 --> 00:12:01,220
And matching sweatsuits.

208
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:04,265
Shoot. I'm so sorry, Covey.

209
00:12:04,348 --> 00:12:07,101
Something came up. I've just been so busy.

210
00:12:07,184 --> 00:12:09,228
Gigi and I have
an emergency wardrobe meeting.

211
00:12:09,311 --> 00:12:11,647
Eunice vetoed all her costumes.

212
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:14,483
Oh, uh, that sounds so stressful.
I'm sorry.

213
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:17,194
Yes, but luckily, Gigi's quite talented.

214
00:12:17,278 --> 00:12:19,321
She's already putting together
a whole new concept.

215
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:21,741
Wow. Gigi to the rescue.

216
00:12:22,908 --> 00:12:24,660
What is the story with you two anyway?

217
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:27,246
Uh, we've basically been friends
since we were toddlers.

218
00:12:27,329 --> 00:12:30,875
Gigi's mum's an actress too.
We used to mess around the red carpets.

219
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:34,545
Sounds glamorous. When was
the last time you two saw each other?

220
00:12:35,463 --> 00:12:38,132
Don't know.
Before she left for FIT, I guess.

221
00:12:40,217 --> 00:12:42,595
- What's with all the questions?
- Mm.

222
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:44,680
I'm gonna go.

223
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:54,190
Marius told me
that Gigi was your first love.

224
00:12:55,274 --> 00:12:59,987
And it made me feel kinda weird
watching you be all goofy around her.

225
00:13:00,070 --> 00:13:04,909
With all your inside jokes,
and, well, she is unnervingly cool.

226
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:10,039
You have nothing to worry about.

227
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:13,459
Whatever feelings I had, it's in the past.

228
00:13:13,542 --> 00:13:16,504
And whatever you and I have
is in the present.

229
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:20,966
And besides,
if it wasn't for the costume crisis,

230
00:13:21,842 --> 00:13:25,805
I'd be on the perfect spa date
with my perfect girl.

231
00:13:27,139 --> 00:13:28,516
That's you, by the way.

232
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:32,353
I might even wear that fire hazard.

233
00:13:32,436 --> 00:13:35,564
I promise not to let you
walk past any open flames.

234
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:36,649
Mm.

235
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:41,237
Mm.

236
00:13:48,035 --> 00:13:48,994
See you at the shoot.

237
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:50,955
<i>If I'm gonna be a good girlfriend,</i>

238
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:53,040
<i>I need to be there for Min Ho</i>
<i>this weekend.</i>

239
00:13:53,123 --> 00:13:57,211
<i>Which means I need to win Jiwon over</i>
<i>with a perfect date of her own.</i>

240
00:14:02,842 --> 00:14:06,512
Jiwon! I heard some teachers
are going to the Cat Café this weekend.

241
00:14:06,595 --> 00:14:08,514
- Maybe you and Alex could--
- No, thank you.

242
00:14:08,597 --> 00:14:10,683
- What about gelato?
- Uh, I have grading.

243
00:14:13,018 --> 00:14:15,312
Have you heard of Baby Moo Moo?

244
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:17,815
Baby Moo Moo? Who hasn't?
She's the hottest ticket in Seoul.

245
00:14:17,898 --> 00:14:19,817
The entire aquarium is sold out for weeks.

246
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:21,777
What if I told you I could get you in?

247
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:24,697
Then would you give me
a tiny extension on that essay?

248
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:26,657
For a national treasure?

249
00:14:27,992 --> 00:14:32,830
Oh my gosh. I cannot believe
I get to see Baby Moo Moo!

250
00:14:32,913 --> 00:14:34,665
I mean, it's no Australian Dugong,

251
00:14:34,748 --> 00:14:37,626
which I understand
is a close cousin to the manatee.

252
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:40,254
And speaking of cousins…

253
00:14:40,337 --> 00:14:41,547
What?

254
00:14:41,630 --> 00:14:43,841
Professor Finnerty,
what are you doing here?

255
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:46,093
Kitty invited me.

256
00:14:46,176 --> 00:14:48,429
I didn't know you'd be here.
What a pleasant surprise.

257
00:14:48,512 --> 00:14:49,471
Ah.

258
00:14:50,097 --> 00:14:53,475
Please tell me this isn't
some kind of secret blind date.

259
00:14:54,226 --> 00:14:56,645
Well, I should be getting to set now.

260
00:14:56,729 --> 00:14:59,148
But you two get your Moo Moo on.

261
00:14:59,231 --> 00:15:00,983
I will, uh, check in later.

262
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:03,110
Have fun.

263
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,031
<i>Action!</i>

264
00:15:10,492 --> 00:15:13,954
<i>At the start you had my heart</i>
<i>Oh, you were my everything! </i>

265
00:15:14,038 --> 00:15:18,334
<i>Then you tried to dull my light</i>
<i>Your mistake, ugh, boring! </i>

266
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:22,046
<i>I can't be tamed, don't say my name</i>
<i>'Cause I'm your only claim to fame </i>

267
00:15:22,129 --> 00:15:24,214
<i>I'm too smart, too hot</i>
<i>Too busy, too pretty </i>

268
00:15:24,298 --> 00:15:26,091
<i>To get caught up in your games </i>

269
00:15:26,175 --> 00:15:28,177
<i>All the boys wanna see me </i>

270
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:29,803
<i>All the girls wanna be me </i>

271
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:31,013
<i>At the end of the night </i>

272
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:33,766
<i>All the guys and the girls</i>
<i>Close their eyes and dream me </i>

273
00:15:33,849 --> 00:15:35,517
<i>It ain't surprising </i>

274
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:37,686
<i>I'm hypnotizing </i>

275
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:40,606
<i>I get them so excited when they dream </i>

276
00:15:40,689 --> 00:15:41,774
'<i>Cause I'm Euniq! </i>

277
00:15:41,857 --> 00:15:43,233
- Cut!
- Cut!

278
00:15:44,193 --> 00:15:46,987
<i>Okay, Kitty. Be cool.</i>

279
00:15:47,071 --> 00:15:49,448
<i>Oh God. I didn't overdress, did I?</i>

280
00:15:50,032 --> 00:15:52,326
Hey, Kitty. You look amazing.

281
00:15:52,409 --> 00:15:53,661
Oh, this? It's nothing.

282
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:56,747
Oh, well, I go full dirtbag
on shoot days, so…

283
00:15:57,998 --> 00:16:00,834
<i>Confirming. I overdressed. Crap.</i>

284
00:16:00,918 --> 00:16:01,794
Um…

285
00:16:01,877 --> 00:16:03,462
- Hi.
- Oh, this is Yuri.

286
00:16:03,545 --> 00:16:05,130
- Hi.
- She volunteered to help today.

287
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:08,342
And I'm also willing to work for money

288
00:16:08,425 --> 00:16:10,636
if you're still looking
for a third assistant.

289
00:16:10,719 --> 00:16:13,472
Oh, also, I saw on Instagram
that you like iced turmeric lattes.

290
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:17,935
You must have scrolled really far back.
I think I got this, like, a year ago?

291
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:20,688
But… thanks.

292
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:23,065
Okay, I'm gonna be over there.

293
00:16:24,316 --> 00:16:26,193
Uh, have you seen Min Ho?

294
00:16:26,276 --> 00:16:27,403
Yeah, they're over there,

295
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:30,322
arguing about whether or not
Tae-Oh should be wearing a shirt.

296
00:16:30,406 --> 00:16:31,782
Got it.

297
00:16:31,865 --> 00:16:34,952
This is such a big day for Min Ho.
I just want everything to go well.

298
00:16:35,035 --> 00:16:39,331
I'm sure, especially after all that stuff
with Eunice's dress on the yacht.

299
00:16:39,415 --> 00:16:40,374
Uh, Marius told me.

300
00:16:40,457 --> 00:16:43,127
Hmm. Well, it was
an honest mistake, I swear.

301
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:44,211
Obviously.

302
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:50,718
Uh, I… I think that's my cue.

303
00:16:50,801 --> 00:16:52,302
Maybe I can help too.

304
00:16:55,389 --> 00:16:58,434
Why would you be shirtless in an aquarium?

305
00:16:58,517 --> 00:16:59,852
Do I have to say it?

306
00:17:00,644 --> 00:17:01,603
Ah.

307
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:04,273
Tae-Oh, I understand what you're saying.

308
00:17:04,356 --> 00:17:08,027
But Yisoo made this tank top
especially for you.

309
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:09,403
Really?

310
00:17:09,486 --> 00:17:12,990
<i>If they were arguing</i>
<i>in English, I'd problem-solve this.</i>

311
00:17:13,073 --> 00:17:17,161
<i>But they're not, so I need to figure out</i>
<i>how else to make myself useful.</i>

312
00:17:22,791 --> 00:17:24,209
What are you doing here?

313
00:17:24,293 --> 00:17:26,670
The same as you. I'm supporting Min Ho.

314
00:17:26,754 --> 00:17:29,673
Please, the only reason
you're supportive is if it benefits you.

315
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:32,676
As if you're here
purely out of the goodness of your heart.

316
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,511
What other reason would I have?

317
00:17:34,595 --> 00:17:38,474
I don't know. Gee, maybe you wanted
to take a selfie with Baby Moo Moo.

318
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:43,270
Okay, maybe I had
an impromptu photo shoot this morning.

319
00:17:43,353 --> 00:17:45,689
Well, I mean, no one can blame you.
She is cute.

320
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:49,318
And you have a knack
for taking a one-of-a-kind self-portrait.

321
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:55,324
You deleted the pic I sent you
this summer like you promised, right?

322
00:17:55,407 --> 00:17:58,243
Q, relax. You can trust me.

323
00:18:04,124 --> 00:18:05,918
<i>Thought I wouldn't go far</i>
<i>But I'm a star </i>

324
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:07,961
<i>You thought you hurt me</i>
<i>But boy, I'm in charge </i>

325
00:18:08,045 --> 00:18:10,130
<i>While you chase girls</i>
<i>Who wish they were me </i>

326
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:11,924
<i>I'll be trapping boys like Jay Park </i>

327
00:18:12,007 --> 00:18:13,175
<i>All the boys wanna see me </i>

328
00:18:13,258 --> 00:18:14,551
Cut!

329
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:16,678
This isn't working, and we're late.

330
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:19,556
I hate this choreo!

331
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,016
Well, it's too late to change it.

332
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:24,520
Okay, then can we
at least take five? I have to pee.

333
00:18:24,603 --> 00:18:26,063
Can't you just hold it?

334
00:18:26,146 --> 00:18:29,525
No, not when we're surrounded by water!

335
00:18:29,608 --> 00:18:32,903
Can somebody please get me green juice?

336
00:18:32,986 --> 00:18:36,448
That will just make you pee even more.

337
00:18:36,532 --> 00:18:39,785
- I've never seen her like this.
- Hey, don't worry. I will get her juice.

338
00:18:39,868 --> 00:18:41,703
Min Ho, I think I know what's wrong.

339
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:45,249
Eunice and Tae-Oh probably hooked up
on tour, now she feels weird around him.

340
00:18:45,332 --> 00:18:46,542
Are you serious?

341
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:50,879
If their fans figure this out,
both their careers will be ruined.

342
00:18:50,963 --> 00:18:52,965
And my dad will kill me.
My dad will kill me.

343
00:18:53,048 --> 00:18:55,342
Hey, hey, hey.
Don't worry. I think I have an idea.

344
00:19:03,183 --> 00:19:04,726
Have you seen where Min Ho went?

345
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:07,396
Yeah, he just went along with Gige.

346
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:10,899
I'm glad I got them back together.
They make a brilliant team, don't they?

347
00:19:30,878 --> 00:19:32,921
You're watching
Baby Moo Moo do the backstroke,

348
00:19:33,005 --> 00:19:34,673
and you're not even smiling.

349
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:36,383
Something's up.

350
00:19:37,176 --> 00:19:38,927
Gigi was Min Ho's first love.

351
00:19:40,137 --> 00:19:43,182
Dae was your first love.
You got over him, right?

352
00:19:43,265 --> 00:19:45,893
No, but Gigi and Min Ho
still have a connection.

353
00:19:45,976 --> 00:19:48,020
I've been watching them all day

354
00:19:48,103 --> 00:19:51,523
and I don't know how to be there
for Min Ho. Not like she does.

355
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:53,483
I wish Marius never even told me.

356
00:19:54,776 --> 00:19:58,280
Wait. You're telling me Marius
put Gigi and Min Ho back in touch

357
00:19:58,363 --> 00:20:00,490
and made sure
you knew about their history?

358
00:20:01,325 --> 00:20:04,786
This guy loves leveraging secrets
to mess with people.

359
00:20:06,830 --> 00:20:09,374
- Oh my God, I'm so screwed!
- Oh my God, I'm being played.

360
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:10,542
You first.

361
00:20:10,626 --> 00:20:14,087
Marius is totally just using Gigi
to make me feel insecure about Min Ho,

362
00:20:14,171 --> 00:20:15,631
and gaslighting me.

363
00:20:15,714 --> 00:20:19,176
But that ends now.
I am not being sidelined. Okay, your turn.

364
00:20:19,259 --> 00:20:21,637
So, over the summer
I may have sent Marius a photo

365
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:24,181
that you don't send when
you're in a committed relationship.

366
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:26,183
- Q!
- I know, and I'm not proud of it.

367
00:20:26,266 --> 00:20:28,185
And it's not an excuse, but…

368
00:20:29,186 --> 00:20:32,356
Jin hadn't visited me at USC,
and I was super lonely.

369
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:36,235
Marius told me he deleted the photo,
but I don't know if I believe him.

370
00:20:36,318 --> 00:20:38,320
If he wants to mess with
your relationship,

371
00:20:38,403 --> 00:20:39,613
that photo's gonna do it.

372
00:20:39,696 --> 00:20:42,241
And if you don't want Marius
leveraging that against you,

373
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:45,786
I think you have to tell Jin the truth.
There's no other way.

374
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:50,415
Okay. Wish me luck.

375
00:20:56,964 --> 00:20:59,841
What are you doing?
You can't iron silk on high heat.

376
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:02,386
Oh my God, I'm so sorry. I didn't know.

377
00:21:02,469 --> 00:21:04,096
My maid used to do this for me.

378
00:21:04,179 --> 00:21:06,515
This was our only backup dress.

379
00:21:07,182 --> 00:21:10,769
I get that you want to help, but… don't.

380
00:21:13,355 --> 00:21:15,190
Oh. Sorry.

381
00:21:15,274 --> 00:21:16,817
Hey, is Eunice around?

382
00:21:17,401 --> 00:21:18,402
What's that?

383
00:21:18,986 --> 00:21:21,238
Macarons. I ordered them overnight.

384
00:21:21,321 --> 00:21:23,573
Eunice loved them on her Paris tour stop.

385
00:21:23,657 --> 00:21:27,869
I just wanted to remind her
what she's working so hard for.

386
00:21:28,412 --> 00:21:32,207
- Are you okay?
- No, I totally messed up.

387
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:34,876
There's no way I'm getting this job now.

388
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:41,341
Hey, if you want this job
half as much as I want Eunice back,

389
00:21:41,425 --> 00:21:42,926
don't give up.

390
00:21:43,010 --> 00:21:44,344
Wish me luck.

391
00:21:45,429 --> 00:21:46,430
<i>Action!</i>

392
00:21:46,513 --> 00:21:48,348
<i>You </i>

393
00:21:48,432 --> 00:21:49,850
- Cut!
- Cut!

394
00:21:49,933 --> 00:21:52,978
Oh my God. I'm so sorry, guys.
I thought that was on silent.

395
00:21:53,061 --> 00:21:56,898
- Q, we are already delayed.
- You are so right.

396
00:21:56,982 --> 00:21:59,067
Guys, no more delays. Come on.

397
00:21:59,151 --> 00:22:00,610
Phones in the bin.

398
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:02,779
Hey, you signed an NDA.

399
00:22:03,655 --> 00:22:06,199
Um… thanks. Thank you.

400
00:22:06,283 --> 00:22:09,161
Thank you, Dae.
Always a team player. You too.

401
00:22:09,953 --> 00:22:13,290
Oh, thank you, guys.
You'll get it at the end of the day.

402
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:16,501
All right, listen up, everyone!

403
00:22:17,210 --> 00:22:19,838
Gigi, Eunice, and I
just worked out a new scene.

404
00:22:19,921 --> 00:22:24,092
All right, the song "EUNIQ"
is about a unique woman, not a man.

405
00:22:24,176 --> 00:22:26,053
By the way, brilliant idea, Gige.

406
00:22:26,636 --> 00:22:31,099
So, Tae-Oh will be in the background,
and can someone get my star a fresh juice?

407
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:34,394
- <i>That's my cue!</i>
- I got it.

408
00:22:38,065 --> 00:22:40,275
Are you kidding me? Dude…

409
00:22:42,444 --> 00:22:45,489
- Are you okay?
- I am so sorry.

410
00:22:45,572 --> 00:22:48,867
I can't believe I'm doing this again.
Please, please let me help.

411
00:22:48,950 --> 00:22:51,161
Maybe you shouldn't, Covey.

412
00:22:51,870 --> 00:22:53,246
Gigi, can you fix this?

413
00:22:53,330 --> 00:22:56,625
- No, I'm not a designer.
- I can fix the dress.

414
00:22:57,709 --> 00:22:59,378
Yes, yes, great idea.

415
00:22:59,461 --> 00:23:02,172
If anybody can turn this dress
into something incredible, it's Yuri.

416
00:23:02,255 --> 00:23:04,091
Let me try. I know what I'm doing.

417
00:23:04,174 --> 00:23:07,427
And frankly,
we don't really have any other choice.

418
00:23:20,524 --> 00:23:22,067
Please, allow me.

419
00:23:25,612 --> 00:23:26,905
I told you I deleted it.

420
00:23:26,988 --> 00:23:28,657
I'm just supposed to believe you?

421
00:23:29,699 --> 00:23:31,368
You thrive on chaos.

422
00:23:31,451 --> 00:23:34,329
You reached out to Gigi to mess
with Kitty and Min Ho's relationship.

423
00:23:34,413 --> 00:23:36,248
Yeah, because Kitty
messed with ours first.

424
00:23:36,331 --> 00:23:40,293
For the last time,
we're not in a relationship. I'm with Jin.

425
00:23:40,377 --> 00:23:43,755
I deleted the picture, but you can't
delete the fact that you sent it.

426
00:23:43,839 --> 00:23:46,049
Obviously, you still have
feelings for me, Q.

427
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:48,301
I don't know
why you're so afraid to admit that.

428
00:23:56,059 --> 00:23:58,812
<i>'Cause I'm Euniq, Euniq, Euniq</i>

429
00:23:58,895 --> 00:24:00,939
<i>She's fine, I guess, but can't compete </i>

430
00:24:01,022 --> 00:24:02,774
Is that that kid's shirt?

431
00:24:02,858 --> 00:24:05,152
Yep, I dyed Dae's shirt
with the green juice,

432
00:24:05,235 --> 00:24:09,197
and the yellow is from the iced turmeric
latte you didn't take a single sip of.

433
00:24:09,281 --> 00:24:14,369
You know, any kiss-ass can buy coffee,
but it takes real talent to save a dress.

434
00:24:14,453 --> 00:24:16,997
If you wanna be Yisoo's third assistant,
I'll get you an interview.

435
00:24:18,457 --> 00:24:19,749
<i>Euniq, hey! </i>

436
00:24:20,876 --> 00:24:24,004
Cut! Okay, that's a wrap!

437
00:24:24,087 --> 00:24:26,339
- Eunice! Here--
- Thank you so much!

438
00:24:29,509 --> 00:24:32,679
Hey, you think I can meet up
with Eunice later?

439
00:24:32,762 --> 00:24:33,889
Ah…

440
00:24:34,556 --> 00:24:37,476
I'm not sure.
She seems pretty busy, don't you think?

441
00:24:38,602 --> 00:24:41,897
Then, can you give her these macarons?
I want her to know--

442
00:24:41,980 --> 00:24:45,901
Dae, I don't know how to say this…

443
00:24:48,361 --> 00:24:51,531
I think Eunice hooked up
with Tae-Oh on tour.

444
00:24:51,615 --> 00:24:52,657
I'm sorry.

445
00:24:55,035 --> 00:24:57,621
No, thanks for telling me.

446
00:25:07,589 --> 00:25:08,798
- Hey.
- Hey.

447
00:25:09,299 --> 00:25:12,427
I know I've been acting a little crazy.

448
00:25:13,553 --> 00:25:15,972
I just wanted to be
a supportive girlfriend

449
00:25:16,056 --> 00:25:17,474
and have your back.

450
00:25:17,557 --> 00:25:20,852
But then, Gigi showed up,
and you guys are so in sync,

451
00:25:20,936 --> 00:25:24,189
and you have all this history
and you just seem,

452
00:25:24,272 --> 00:25:26,066
like, effortless together.

453
00:25:26,149 --> 00:25:27,776
So, I guess I felt…

454
00:25:29,027 --> 00:25:30,862
Threatened?

455
00:25:32,447 --> 00:25:33,448
Don't be.

456
00:25:35,408 --> 00:25:38,578
Kitty, you and I aren't effortless, but…

457
00:25:39,412 --> 00:25:42,582
I do like that you make me do things
I wouldn't normally do.

458
00:25:43,875 --> 00:25:46,586
Like doing that stupid Gangnam dance.

459
00:25:46,670 --> 00:25:48,547
And you do have my back.

460
00:25:48,630 --> 00:25:52,133
You believe in me
more than I believe in myself sometimes.

461
00:25:52,634 --> 00:25:56,805
And sure, maybe you go overboard
now and then, but…

462
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,933
I wouldn't change a thing.

463
00:26:01,351 --> 00:26:02,352
Really?

464
00:26:02,435 --> 00:26:06,022
Yes. And thanks
to that Senior Sunset List,

465
00:26:06,898 --> 00:26:09,192
we're making
some amazing memories together.

466
00:26:09,276 --> 00:26:11,778
Well, I'm happy to do
more things you like too.

467
00:26:12,445 --> 00:26:13,947
You mean like our spa date?

468
00:26:14,739 --> 00:26:17,367
Which I hope is still on.

469
00:26:17,450 --> 00:26:18,785
I'll even wear the sweatsuit.

470
00:26:18,868 --> 00:26:23,206
Well, as much as I would love a massage,

471
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:26,001
I have a ten-page essay due Tuesday.

472
00:26:27,085 --> 00:26:29,129
Tell you what, let me wrap up here,

473
00:26:29,921 --> 00:26:32,882
grab my stuff,
and I'll help you with your essay.

474
00:26:33,508 --> 00:26:36,011
I'll even bring over
some sheet masks while I'm at it.

475
00:26:38,221 --> 00:26:40,515
You got this, and I've got you.

476
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:53,528
Hi, roomies.

477
00:26:53,612 --> 00:26:55,322
You're in a good mood.

478
00:26:55,405 --> 00:26:59,034
I got a job interview with Yisoo.

479
00:26:59,117 --> 00:27:01,119
- Oh my God.
- What? That's sick.

480
00:27:01,202 --> 00:27:04,414
Oh, and I totally ripped off
your coffee move, which worked.

481
00:27:04,497 --> 00:27:05,874
Just not in the way I expected.

482
00:27:05,957 --> 00:27:09,628
You can tell me all the details
over an iced chai when you get the job.

483
00:27:09,711 --> 00:27:12,631
- Okay.
- You've met your match.

484
00:27:12,714 --> 00:27:13,965
Oh my God.

485
00:27:15,550 --> 00:27:18,219
I didn't realize
you two were getting so close.

486
00:27:18,303 --> 00:27:21,514
- Care to catch me up?
- I think we're becoming friends.

487
00:27:21,598 --> 00:27:24,184
- Stay down.
- Oh.

488
00:27:24,267 --> 00:27:26,019
Oh, you… Okay.

489
00:27:26,102 --> 00:27:27,604
You've met your master.

490
00:27:32,108 --> 00:27:34,486
Hey. How'd it go with Alex?

491
00:27:34,569 --> 00:27:36,863
I don't know, Kitty.
He left right after you did.

492
00:27:36,946 --> 00:27:37,906
What? Why?

493
00:27:37,989 --> 00:27:41,159
Because if we'd known this was a setup,
we wouldn't have come.

494
00:27:41,993 --> 00:27:44,120
There are rules against teachers dating.

495
00:27:44,204 --> 00:27:46,706
If Principal Lee found out,
we could be fired.

496
00:27:46,790 --> 00:27:48,958
- I didn't mean to cause--
- I'm not an idiot, Kitty.

497
00:27:49,042 --> 00:27:50,752
I've seen <i>Clueless.</i>

498
00:27:50,835 --> 00:27:53,254
Whatever spark
you think we have doesn't exist.

499
00:27:53,338 --> 00:27:56,383
I find his cheerfulness annoying,
his accent unintelligible,

500
00:27:56,466 --> 00:27:58,468
and his love of boat shoes just deranged.

501
00:27:58,551 --> 00:28:01,304
Wow, okay. I thought
the preppy look kind of worked for him--

502
00:28:01,388 --> 00:28:05,016
Stop. This isn't about me and Alex at all.

503
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:06,685
It's about you.

504
00:28:06,768 --> 00:28:09,813
You manipulated me so you could
spend more time with your boyfriend,

505
00:28:09,896 --> 00:28:12,315
who I still think
you're too focused on, by the way.

506
00:28:12,399 --> 00:28:15,193
And you put my job in danger, again.

507
00:28:15,276 --> 00:28:17,570
You definitely don't have
your priorities straight,

508
00:28:17,654 --> 00:28:19,572
so I'm gonna help you with that.

509
00:28:19,656 --> 00:28:23,076
I'm taking back your extension
and adding ten pages to your essay.

510
00:28:23,159 --> 00:28:25,912
No, if I don't pass your class,
I'm not gonna graduate.

511
00:28:25,995 --> 00:28:28,665
Then I suggest you hit the books. Hard.

512
00:28:30,875 --> 00:28:33,253
<i>I was so busy</i>
<i>living in the moment with Min Ho</i>

513
00:28:33,336 --> 00:28:36,548
<i>that I forgot</i>
<i>my actual future is on the line.</i>

514
00:28:36,631 --> 00:28:40,176
<i>If I don't pass Jiwon's class,</i>
<i>I'm screwed.</i>

515
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:42,929
<i>That's the moral of the story, babe</i>

516
00:28:58,111 --> 00:29:02,949
<i>They say it's better to have loved</i>
<i>And lost</i>

517
00:29:03,032 --> 00:29:06,953
<i>Than never to have loved at all</i>

518
00:29:07,036 --> 00:29:09,956
<i>That could be a load of shit</i>

519
00:29:10,540 --> 00:29:15,962
<i>But I just need to tell you all</i>

520
00:29:16,546 --> 00:29:20,967
<i>Some mistakes get made</i>
<i>That's all right, that's okay</i>

521
00:29:21,050 --> 00:29:24,971
<i>You can think that you're in love</i>
<i>When you're really just engaged</i>

522
00:29:25,054 --> 00:29:28,975
<i>Some mistakes get made</i>
<i>That's all right, that's okay</i>

523
00:29:29,058 --> 00:29:32,979
<i>In the end, it's better for me</i>
<i>That's the moral of the story</i>

